---
import Section from './Section.astro';

const faqs = [
  ['Can PumpOS work offline?', 'Yes. The desktop app is designed for offline station operations and syncs when connectivity returns.'],
  ['Can I manage multiple stations?', 'Yes. The model supports multi-station ownership with role-based access and station-level reporting.'],
  ['Can it handle lubricants and accessories?', 'Yes. Fuel sales come from nozzle readings; merchandise and lubricants are tracked as separate manual sales and stock movements.'],
  ['Can my accountant use it?', 'Yes. Accountant access can review ledgers, DSSR snapshots, invoices and financial movements without exposing operator-only actions.'],
  ['Can I import existing data?', 'The roadmap includes onboarding/import support. For early deployments, master data is migrated during setup.'],
  ['How is pricing handled?', 'Pricing will be configured per deployment and module scope. The initial CTA is a live demo, not self-serve checkout.'],
];
---

<Section id="faq" title="Questions owners ask before trusting a new system." lead="PumpOS is built for operational confidence, not a casual trial signup.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl divide-y divide-[var(--color-border-soft)] rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border-soft)] bg-white">
    {faqs.map(([q, a]) => (
      <details class="group p-5">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]">
          {q}
          <span class="text-[var(--color-brand)] transition group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-[var(--color-ink-muted)]">{a}</p>
      </details>
    ))}
  </div>
</Section>
